Step 1. Calculate the Current Ratio.  
• Current Assets (end) = 21,224,639.20  
• Current Liabilities (end) = 727,140.68  
Current Ratio = 21,224,639.20 ÷ 727,140.68 ≈ 29.19  

Step 2. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• Gross Profit = 4,142,813.42  
• Total Revenue = 14,542,813.42  
Gross Profit Margin = (4,142,813.42 ÷ 14,542,813.42) × 100 ≈ 28.49%  

Step 3. Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• Total Liabilities (here only current liabilities) = 727,140.68  
• Total Assets = 29,133,140.32  
Debt to Asset Ratio = 727,140.68 ÷ 29,133,140.32 ≈ 0.02  

Step 4. Calculate the Net Profit Margin.  
• Net Profit = 405,999.64  
• Total Revenue = 14,542,813.42  
Net Profit Margin = (405,999.64 ÷ 14,542,813.42) × 100 ≈ 2.79%  

Step 5. Calculate the Cash to Current Debt Ratio.  
• Cash and Cash Equivalents (ending balance) = 2,582,632.85  
• Current Liabilities = 727,140.68  
Cash to Current Debt Ratio = 2,582,632.85 ÷ 727,140.68 ≈ 3.55  

Step 6. Calculate the Free Cash Flow (FCF).  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –17,417,367.15  
• Cash Flow from Investing Activities = –0.00 (no fixed asset purchase)  
Free Cash Flow (FCF) = –17,417,367.15 – 0 = –17,417,367.15  

Step 7. Calculate the Return on Assets (ROA).  
• Net Profit = 405,999.64  
• Total Assets = 29,133,140.32  
ROA = (405,999.64 ÷ 29,133,140.32) × 100 ≈ 1.39%

Thus, the solution in JSON is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "29.19",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.49%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.02",
    "Net Profit Margin": "2.79%",
    "Cash to Current Debt Ratio": "3.55",
    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "-17417367.15",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "1.39%"
  }
}
